Product Requirements Document
PR Document Helper
Travel History, Address History, Gap Detection, Export-Ready Tables
Summary
PR Document Helper is a small, offline-first tool that helps Canadian immigration applicants build clean, continuous Travel History and Address History tables with automatic gap and overlap detection, then export them as attachment-ready CSV and PDF.
The core pain it solves: IRCC forms and portals often require long date ranges (for example travel history for the last 10 years or since age 18) and expect continuity with no unexplained gaps, but most applicants end up juggling spreadsheets, PDFs, and memory. 
Canada
+2
Canada
+2
Problem Statement
Applicants need to provide accurate, continuous timelines for travel and addresses, often across many years. Manual entry is error-prone, especially for:
gaps (missing months)
overlaps (two addresses covering the same dates)
inconsistent date boundaries (end date earlier than start date)
“I don’t remember exact dates” situations
IRCC guidance includes travel history requirements (IMM 5562) and other sections where IRCC explicitly says to avoid gaps in history tables. 
Canada
+2
Canada
+2
Goals
Make it fast to build Travel History and Address History in the formats applicants actually submit.
Prevent common timeline mistakes before submission (gaps, overlaps, out-of-range entries).
Generate clean exports that can be uploaded as supporting documents.
Non-Goals
Not legal advice, not a replacement for IRCC forms.
No cloud sync in v1.
No automatic retrieval from passports, emails, airlines, or border databases in v1.
No direct “fill IRCC PDF” automation in v1 (maintenance risk, brittle).
Target Users
Primary Persona: DIY PR Applicant
Filling PR portal forms or requested supplementary tables
Has multi-country travel and multiple addresses
Wants confidence their tables have no gaps and export cleanly
Secondary Persona: Immigration Consultant or Lawyer Assistant
Needs standardized client intake tables
Wants consistent exports and fewer back-and-forth corrections
Adjacent Persona: PR Card Renewal and Citizenship-Planners
PR card renewal workflows also include address history requirements with “account for each month” and “leave no gaps” style language. 
Canada
+1

Citizenship applicants often keep travel logs and IRCC provides a travel journal as a memory aid. 
