Competitive Landscape
What Users Use Today
Generic PDF editors / “fill online” sites
They help fill forms online but do not focus on validation, gap detection, or producing standardized attachment tables. 
pdfFiller
+1
Official IRCC tools (adjacent, not PR table builders)
Citizenship physical presence calculator and travel journal help remember trips, but they are not PR travel history table builders. 
eServices
+1
Spreadsheets, templates, and community advice
Forum and Reddit threads show people asking for templates and struggling with what format to use when asked for travel history tables. 
Canadavisa.com
+1

There are also DIY spreadsheet projects (for example a GitHub travel log aimed at citizenship-style tracking), which validates the need but does not package the PR-specific workflow. 
GitHub
Differentiation
PR Document Helper is not “another template”. It is a validator and exporter:
timeline engine that guarantees continuity
“fix it” suggestions (auto-fill missing gap row)
attachment-ready PDF and CSV exports
Product Scope
Core Modules (v1)
Travel History Builder (IRCC style)
Address History Builder (IRCC style)
Timeline Validator (gap, overlap, range checks)
Export Engine (CSV, PDF)
Optional Modules (v1.1+)
Personal History Builder (activities timeline aligned with IRCC expectations for continuous history) 
